<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-275-114  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 275 114.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  March 26 1990 n293 p40(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ABC makes news with fiber. (ABC Radio News Inc. uses privatefiber-optic network)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Schultz, Beth.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>ABC Radio News Inc is supplementing its regular satellite feedswith transmissions over a land-based MCI Communications Corpfiber-optic network.andP;  MCI says ABC Radio is the first radionetwork to use a nationwide private-line network.andP;  ABC Radio cantransmit at 1.544M-bps over MCI's high-capacity TDS 1.5 T1service.andP;  Unlike satellite systems, the fiber optic network allowsthe audio channels to function in both directions.andP;  Recently,research and development investors have neglected audiocommunications, pouring money instead into the development ofvoice, data, video, private-line and cellular services.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Capital Cities-ABC Inc. ABC Radio (communication systems)MCI Communications Corp. (services).andO;Topic:     Fiber OpticsPrivate NetworksT1 CommunicationsRadio Communication.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>